metrics.name: active1DayUsers
metrics.description: The number of distinct active users on your site or app within a 1 day period. The 1 day period includes the last day in the report's date range. Note: this is the same as Active Users.

metrics.name: active28DayUsers
metrics.description: The number of distinct active users on your site or app within a 28 day period. The 28 day period includes the last day in the report's date range.

metrics.name: active7DayUsers
metrics.description: The number of distinct active users on your site or app within a 7 day period. The 7 day period includes the last day in the report's date range.

metrics.name: activeUsers
metrics.description: The number of distinct users who visited your site or app.

metrics.name: adUnitExposure
metrics.description: The time that an ad unit was exposed to a user, in milliseconds.

metrics.name: addToCarts
metrics.description: The number of times users added items to their shopping carts.

metrics.name: advertiserAdClicks
metrics.description: Total number of times users have clicked on an ad to reach the property. Includes clicks from linked integrations like linked Search Ads 360 advertisers. Also includes uploaded clicks from data import.

metrics.name: advertiserAdCost
metrics.description: The total amount you paid for your ads. Includes costs from linked integrations like linked Google Ads accounts. Also includes uploaded cost from data import; to learn more, see Import cost data.

metrics.name: advertiserAdCostPerClick
metrics.description: Ads cost per click is ad cost divided by ad clicks and is often abbreviated CPC.

metrics.name: advertiserAdCostPerKeyEvent
metrics.description: Cost per key event is ad cost divided by key events.

metrics.name: advertiserAdImpressions
metrics.description: The total number of impressions. Includes impressions from linked integrations like linked Display & Video 360 advertisers. Also includes uploaded impressions from data import.

metrics.name: averagePurchaseRevenue
metrics.description: The average purchase revenue in the transaction group of events.

metrics.name: averagePurchaseRevenuePerPayingUser
metrics.description: Average revenue per paying user (ARPPU) is the total purchase revenue per active user that logged a purchase event. The summary metric is for the time period selected.

metrics.name: averagePurchaseRevenuePerUser
metrics.description: The average purchase revenue per active user is the total purchase revenue per active user that logged any event. The summary metric is for the time period selected.

metrics.name: averageRevenuePerUser
metrics.description: Average revenue per active user (ARPU). The summary metric is for the time period selected. ARPU uses Total Revenue and includes AdMob estimated earnings.

metrics.name: averageSessionDuration
metrics.description: The average duration (in seconds) of users` sessions.

metrics.name: bounceRate
metrics.description: The percentage of sessions that were not engaged ((Sessions Minus Engaged sessions) divided by Sessions). This metric is returned as a fraction; for example, 0.2761 means 27.61% of sessions were bounces.

metrics.name: cartToViewRate
metrics.description: The number of users who added a product(s) to their cart divided by the number of users who viewed the same product(s). This metric is returned as a fraction; for example, 0.1132 means 11.32% of users who viewed a product also added the same product to their cart.

metrics.name: checkouts
metrics.description: The number of times users started the checkout process. This metric counts the occurrence of the begin_checkout event.

metrics.name: cohortActiveUsers
metrics.description: The number of users in the cohort who are active in the time window corresponding to the cohort nth day/week/month. For example in the row where cohortNthWeek = 0001, this metric is the number of users (in the cohort) who are active in week 1.

metrics.name: cohortTotalUsers
metrics.description: The total number of users in the cohort. This metric is the same value in every row of the report for each cohort. Because cohorts are defined by a shared acquisition date, cohortTotalUsers is the same as cohortActiveUsers for the cohort's selection date range. For report rows later than the cohort's selection range, it is typical for cohortActiveUsers to be smaller than cohortTotalUsers. This difference represents users from the cohort that were not active for the later date. cohortTotalUsers is commonly used in the metric expression cohortActiveUsers/cohortTotalUsers to compute a user retention fraction for the cohort. The relationship between activeUsers and totalUsers is not equivalent to the relationship between cohortActiveUsers and cohortTotalUsers.

metrics.name: crashAffectedUsers
metrics.description: The number of users that logged a crash in this row of the report. For example if the report is time series by date, this metrics reports total users with at least one crash on this date. Crashes are events with the name "app_exception".

metrics.name: crashFreeUsersRate
metrics.description: The number of users without crash events (in this row of the report) divided by the total number of users. This metric is returned as a fraction; for example, 0.9243 means 92.43% of users were crash-free.

metrics.name: dauPerMau
metrics.description: The rolling percent of 30-day active users who are also 1-day active users. This metric is returned as a fraction; for example, 0.113 means 11.3% of 30-day active users were also 1-day active users.

metrics.name: dauPerWau
metrics.description: The rolling percent of 7-day active users who are also 1-day active users. This metric is returned as a fraction; for example, 0.082 means 8.2% of 7-day active users were also 1-day active users.

metrics.name: ecommercePurchases
metrics.description: The number of times users completed a purchase. This metric counts purchase events; this metric does not count in_app_purchase and subscription events.

metrics.name: engagedSessions
metrics.description: The number of sessions that lasted longer than 10 seconds, or had a key event, or had 2 or more screen views.

metrics.name: engagementRate
metrics.description: The percentage of engaged sessions (Engaged sessions divided by Sessions). This metric is returned as a fraction; for example, 0.7239 means 72.39% of sessions were engaged sessions.

metrics.name: eventCount
metrics.description: The count of events.

metrics.name: eventCountPerUser
metrics.description: The average number of events per user (Event count divided by Active users).

metrics.name: eventValue
metrics.description: The sum of the event parameter named value.

metrics.name: eventsPerSession
metrics.description: The average number of events per session (Event count divided by Sessions).

metrics.name: firstTimePurchaserRate
metrics.description: The percentage of active users who made their first purchase. This metric is returned as a fraction; for example, 0.092 means 9.2% of active users were first time purchasers.

metrics.name: firstTimePurchasers
metrics.description: The number of users that completed their first purchase event.

metrics.name: firstTimePurchasersPerNewUser
metrics.description: The average number of first time purchasers per new user.

metrics.name: grossItemRevenue
metrics.description: The total revenue from items only. Gross item revenue is the product of its price and quantity. Item revenue excludes tax and shipping values; tax & shipping values are specified at the event and not item level. Gross item revenue does not include refunds.

metrics.name: grossPurchaseRevenue
metrics.description: The sum of revenue from purchases made in your app or site. Gross purchase revenue sums the revenue for these events: purchase, ecommerce_purchase, in_app_purchase, app_store_subscription_convert, and app_store_subscription_renew. Purchase revenue is specified by the value parameter in tagging.

metrics.name: itemDiscountAmount
metrics.description: The monetary value of item discounts in eCommerce events. This metric is populated in tagging by the discount item parameter.

metrics.name: itemListClickEvents
metrics.description: The number of times users clicked an item when it appeared in a list. This metric counts the occurrence of the select_item event.

metrics.name: itemListClickThroughRate
metrics.description: The number of users who selected a list(s) divided by the number of users who viewed the same list(s). This metric is returned as a fraction; for example, 0.2145 means 21.45% of users who viewed a list also selected the same list.

metrics.name: itemListViewEvents
metrics.description: The number of times the item list was viewed. This metric counts the occurrence of the view_item_list event.

metrics.name: itemPromotionClickThroughRate
metrics.description: The number of users who selected a promotion(s) divided by the number of users who viewed the same promotion(s). This metric is returned as a fraction; for example, 0.1382 means 13.82% of users who viewed a promotion also selected the promotion.

metrics.name: itemRefundAmount
metrics.description: Item refund amount is the total refunded transaction revenue from items only. Item refund amount is the product of price and quantity for the refund event.

metrics.name: itemRevenue
metrics.description: The total revenue from purchases minus refunded transaction revenue from items only. Item revenue is the product of its price and quantity. Item revenue excludes tax and shipping values; tax & shipping values are specified at the event and not item level.

metrics.name: itemViewEvents
metrics.description: The number of times the item details were viewed. The metric counts the occurrence of the view_item event.

metrics.name: itemsAddedToCart
metrics.description: The number of units added to cart for a single item. This metric counts the quantity of items in add_to_cart events.

metrics.name: itemsCheckedOut
metrics.description: The number of units checked out for a single item. This metric counts the quantity of items in begin_checkout events.

metrics.name: itemsClickedInList
metrics.description: The number of units clicked in list for a single item. This metric counts the quantity of items in select_item events.

metrics.name: itemsClickedInPromotion
metrics.description: The number of units clicked in promotion for a single item. This metric counts the quantity of items in select_promotion events.

metrics.name: itemsPurchased
metrics.description: The number of units for a single item included in purchase events. This metric counts the quantity of items in purchase events.

metrics.name: itemsViewed
metrics.description: The number of units viewed for a single item. This metric counts the quantity of items in view_item events.

metrics.name: itemsViewedInList
metrics.description: The number of units viewed in list for a single item. This metric counts the quantity of items in view_item_list events.

metrics.name: itemsViewedInPromotion
metrics.description: The number of units viewed in promotion for a single item. This metric counts the quantity of items in view_promotion events.

metrics.name: keyEvents
metrics.description: The count of key events. Marking an event as a key event affects reports from time of creation. It doesn't change historic data. You can mark any event as key in Google Analytics, and some events (such as first_open or purchase) are marked as key events by default.

metrics.name: newUsers
metrics.description: The number of users who interacted with your site or launched your app for the first time (event triggered: first_open or first_visit).

metrics.name: organicGoogleSearchAveragePosition
metrics.description: The average ranking of your website URLs for the query reported from Search Console. For example, if your site's URL appears at position 3 for one query and position 7 for another query, the average position would be 5 (3+7/2). This metric requires an active Search Console link.

metrics.name: organicGoogleSearchClickThroughRate
metrics.displayName: Organic Google Search click through rate
metrics.description: The organic Google Search click through rate reported from Search Console. Click through rate is clicks per impression. This metric is returned as a fraction; for example, 0.0588 means about 5.88% of impressions resulted in a click. This metric requires an active Search Console link.

metrics.name: organicGoogleSearchClicks
metrics.description: The number of organic Google Search clicks reported from Search Console. This metric requires an active Search Console link.

metrics.name: organicGoogleSearchImpressions
metrics.description: The number of organic Google Search impressions reported from Search Console. This metric requires an active Search Console link.

metrics.name: promotionClicks
metrics.description: The number of times an item promotion was clicked. This metric counts the occurrence of the select_promotion event.

metrics.name: promotionViews
metrics.description: The number of times an item promotion was viewed. This metric counts the occurrence of the view_promotion event.

metrics.name: publisherAdClicks
metrics.description: The number of ad_click events.

metrics.name: publisherAdImpressions
metrics.description: The number of ad_impression events.

metrics.name: purchaseRevenue
metrics.description: The sum of revenue from purchases minus refunded transaction revenue made in your app or site. Purchase revenue sums the revenue for these events: purchase, ecommerce_purchase, in_app_purchase, app_store_subscription_convert, and app_store_subscription_renew. Purchase revenue is specified by the value parameter in tagging.

metrics.name: purchaseToViewRate
metrics.description: The number of users who purchased a product(s) divided by the number of users who viewed the same product(s). This metric is returned as a fraction; for example, 0.128 means 12.8% of users that viewed a product(s) also purchased the same product(s).

metrics.name: purchaserRate
metrics.description: The percentage of active users who made 1 or more purchase transactions. This metric is returned as a fraction; for example, 0.412 means 41.2% of users were purchasers.

metrics.name: refundAmount
metrics.description: The total refunded transaction revenues. Refund amount sums refunded revenue for the refund and app_store_refund events.

metrics.name: returnOnAdSpend
metrics.description: Return On Ad Spend (ROAS) is total revenue divided by advertiser ad cost.

metrics.name: screenPageViews
metrics.description: The number of app screens or web pages your users viewed. Repeated views of a single page or screen are counted. (screen_view + page_view events).

metrics.name: screenPageViewsPerSession
metrics.description: The number of app screens or web pages your users viewed per session. Repeated views of a single page or screen are counted. (screen_view + page_view events) / sessions.

metrics.name: screenPageViewsPerUser
metrics.description: The number of app screens or web pages your users viewed per active user. Repeated views of a single page or screen are counted. (screen_view + page_view events) / active users.

metrics.name: scrolledUsers
metrics.description: The number of unique users who scrolled down at least 90% of the page.

metrics.name: sessionKeyEventRate
metrics.description: The percentage of sessions in which any key event was triggered.

metrics.name: sessions
metrics.description: The number of sessions that began on your site or app (event triggered: session_start).

metrics.name: sessionsPerUser
metrics.description: The average number of sessions per user (Sessions divided by Active Users).

metrics.name: shippingAmount
metrics.description: Shipping amount associated with a transaction. Populated by the shipping event parameter.

metrics.name: taxAmount
metrics.description: Tax amount associated with a transaction. Populated by the tax event parameter.

metrics.name: totalAdRevenue
metrics.description: The total advertising revenue from both Admob and third-party sources.

metrics.name: totalPurchasers
metrics.description: The number of users that logged purchase events for the time period selected.

metrics.name: totalRevenue
metrics.description: The sum of revenue from purchases, subscriptions, and advertising (Purchase revenue plus Subscription revenue plus Ad revenue) minus refunded transaction revenue.

metrics.name: totalUsers
metrics.description: The number of distinct users who have logged at least one event, regardless of whether the site or app was in use when that event was logged.

metrics.name: transactions
metrics.description: The count of transaction events with purchase revenue. Transaction events are in_app_purchase, ecommerce_purchase, purchase, app_store_subscription_renew, app_store_subscription_convert, and refund.

metrics.name: transactionsPerPurchaser
metrics.description: The average number of transactions per purchaser.

metrics.name: userEngagementDuration
metrics.description: The total amount of time (in seconds) your website or app was in the foreground of users` devices.

metrics.name: userKeyEventRate
metrics.description: The percentage of users who triggered any key event.

metrics.name: wauPerMau
metrics.description: The rolling percent of 30-day active users who are also 7-day active users. This metric is returned as a fraction; for example, 0.234 means 23.4% of 30-day active users were also 7-day active users.

dimensions.name: achievementId
dimensions.description: The achievement ID in a game for an event. Populated by the event parameter achievement_id.

dimensions.name: adFormat
dimensions.description: Describes the way ads looked and where they were located. Typical formats include Interstitial, Banner, Rewarded, and Native advanced.

dimensions.name: adSourceName
dimensions.description: The source network that served the ad. Typical sources include AdMob Network, Liftoff, Facebook Audience Network, and Mediated house ads.

dimensions.name: adUnitName
dimensions.description: The name you chose to describe this Ad unit. Ad units are containers you place in your apps to show ads to users.

dimensions.name: appVersion
dimensions.description: The app's versionName (Android) or short bundle version (iOS).

dimensions.name: audienceId
dimensions.description: The numeric identifier of an Audience. Users are reported in the audiences to which they belonged during the report's date range. Current user behavior does not affect historical audience membership in reports.

dimensions.name: audienceName
dimensions.description: The given name of an Audience. Users are reported in the audiences to which they belonged during the report's date range. Current user behavior does not affect historical audience membership in reports.

dimensions.name: audienceResourceName
dimensions.description: The resource name of this audience. Resource names contain both collection & resource identifiers to uniquely identify a resource; to learn more, see Resource names.

dimensions.name: brandingInterest
dimensions.description: Interests demonstrated by users who are higher in the shopping funnel. Users can be counted in multiple interest categories. For example, Shoppers, Lifestyles & Hobbies/Pet Lovers, or Travel/Travel Buffs/Beachbound Travelers.

dimensions.name: browser
dimensions.description: The browsers used to view your website.

dimensions.name: campaignId
dimensions.description: The identifier of the marketing campaign. Present only for key events. Includes Google Ads Campaigns, Manual Campaigns, & other Campaigns.

dimensions.name: campaignName
dimensions.description: The name of the marketing campaign. Present only for key events. Includes Google Ads Campaigns, Manual Campaigns, & other Campaigns.

dimensions.name: character
dimensions.description: The player character in a game for an event. Populated by the event parameter character.

dimensions.name: city
dimensions.description: The city from which the user activity originated.

dimensions.name: cityId
dimensions.description: The geographic ID of the city from which the user activity originated, derived from their IP address.

dimensions.name: cm360AccountId
dimensions.description: The CM360 Account ID that led to the key event. Identifies the CM360 Account.

dimensions.name: cm360AccountName
dimensions.description: The CM360 Account Name that led to the key event. A CM360 account consists of advertisers, sites, campaigns, and user profiles.

dimensions.name: cm360AdvertiserId
dimensions.description: The CM360 Advertiser ID that led to the key event. A CM360 Advertiser contains a group of campaigns, creative assets, and other settings.

dimensions.name: cm360AdvertiserName
dimensions.description: The CM360 Advertiser Name that led to the key event. A CM360 Advertiser contains a group of campaigns, creative assets, and other settings.

dimensions.name: cm360CampaignId
dimensions.description: The CM360 Campaign ID that led to the key event. A CM360 campaign can be configured to specify when your ads run, what landing pages are used, and other properties.

dimensions.name: cm360CampaignName
dimensions.description: The CM360 Campaign Name that led to the key event. A CM360 campaign can be configured to specify when your ads run, what landing pages are used, and other properties.

dimensions.name: cm360CreativeFormat
dimensions.description: The CM360 Creative Format that led to the key event. CM360 creative formats are also referred to as creative types.

dimensions.name: cm360CreativeId
dimensions.description: The CM360 Creative ID that led to the key event. Identifies a CM360 creative.

dimensions.name: cm360CreativeName
dimensions.description: The CM360 Creative Name that led to the key event. The name given to a CM360 creative.

dimensions.name: cm360CreativeType
dimensions.description: The CM360 Creative Type that led to the key event. A category of CM360 creatives like 'Display' or 'Tracking'. To learn more, see manage creatives

dimensions.name: cm360CreativeTypeId
dimensions.description: The CM360 Creative Type ID that led to the key event. Identifies a CM360 creative type.

dimensions.name: cm360CreativeVersion
dimensions.description: The CM360 Creative Version that led to the key event. The version number helps you keep track of multiple versions of your creative in your reports. If you upload a new asset to an existing creative, the version number is increased by one.

dimensions.name: cm360Medium
dimensions.description: The CM360 Medium that led to the key event. The CM360 medium is also referred to as the placement cost structure.

dimensions.name: cm360PlacementCostStructure
dimensions.description: The CM360 Placement Cost Structure that led to the key event. Placement cost structures regulate how media cost will be calculated. For example 'CPM'.

dimensions.name: cm360PlacementId
dimensions.description: The CM360 Placement ID that led to the key event. Identifies a CM360 placement. A placement is the part of a website where your ad appears.

dimensions.name: cm360PlacementName
dimensions.description: The CM360 Placement Name that led to the key event. The given name for a CM360 placement. A placement is the part of a website where your ad appears.

dimensions.name: cm360RenderingId
dimensions.description: The CM360 Rendering ID that led to the key event. Identifies a CM360 creative.

dimensions.name: cm360SiteId
dimensions.description: The CM360 Site ID that led to the key event. Identifies a CM360 site.

dimensions.name: cm360SiteName
dimensions.description: The CM360 Site Name that led to the key event. The CM360 Site name from which the ad space was purchased.

dimensions.name: cm360Source
dimensions.description: The CM360 Source that led to the key event. The CM360 source is also referred to as the site name.

dimensions.name: cm360SourceMedium
dimensions.description: The CM360 Source Medium that led to the key event. A combination of the source and medium.

dimensions.name: cohort
dimensions.description: The cohort's name in the request. A cohort is a set of users who started using your website or app in any consecutive group of days. If a cohort name is not specified in the request, cohorts are named by their zero based index such as cohort_0 and cohort_1.

dimensions.name: cohortNthDay
dimensions.description: Day offset relative to the firstSessionDate for the users in the cohort. For example, if a cohort is selected with the start and end date of 2020-03-01, then for the date 2020-03-02, cohortNthDay will be 0001.

dimensions.name: cohortNthMonth
dimensions.description: Month offset relative to the firstSessionDate for the users in the cohort. Month boundaries align with calendar month boundaries. For example, if a cohort is selected with the start and end date in March 2020, then for any date in April 2020, cohortNthMonth will be 0001.

dimensions.name: cohortNthWeek
dimensions.description: Week offset relative to the firstSessionDate for the users in the cohort. Weeks start on Sunday and end on Saturday. For example, if a cohort is selected with the start and end date in the range 2020-11-08 to 2020-11-14, then for the dates in the range 2020-11-15 to 2020-11-21, cohortNthWeek will be 0001.

dimensions.name: contentGroup
dimensions.description: A category that applies to items of published content. Populated by the event parameter content_group.

dimensions.name: contentId
dimensions.description: The identifier of the selected content. Populated by the event parameter content_id.

dimensions.name: contentType
dimensions.description: The category of the selected content. Populated by the event parameter content_type.

dimensions.name: continent
dimensions.description: The continent from which the user activity originated. For example, Americas or Asia.

dimensions.name: continentId
dimensions.description: The geographic ID of the continent from which the user activity originated, derived from their IP address.

dimensions.name: country
dimensions.description: The country from which the user activity originated.

dimensions.name: countryId
dimensions.description: The geographic ID of the country from which the user activity originated, derived from their IP address. Formatted according to ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 standard.

dimensions.name: currencyCode
dimensions.description: The local currency code (based on ISO 4217 standard) of the eCommerce event. For example, USD or GBP. Currency is specified in tagging by the currency parameter. Businesses that transact in more than one currency can specify a local currency code when sending eCommerce events to Analytics, and this dimension shows those currencies. To Learn more, See Currency reference.

dimensions.name: date
dimensions.description: The date of the event, formatted as YYYYMMDD.

dimensions.name: dateHour
dimensions.description: The combined values of date and hour formatted as YYYYMMDDHH.

dimensions.name: dateHourMinute
dimensions.description: The combined values of date, hour, and minute formatted as YYYYMMDDHHMM.

dimensions.name: day
dimensions.description: The day of the month, a two-digit number from 01 to 31.

dimensions.name: dayOfWeek
dimensions.description: The integer day of the week. It returns values in the range 0 to 6 with Sunday as the first day of the week.

dimensions.name: dayOfWeekName
dimensions.description: The day of the week in English. This dimension has values such as Sunday or Monday.

dimensions.name: defaultChannelGroup
dimensions.description: The key event's default channel group is based primarily on source and medium. An enumeration which includes Direct, Organic Search, Paid Social, Organic Social, Email, Affiliates, Referral, Paid Search, Video, and Display.

dimensions.name: deviceCategory
dimensions.description: The type of device: Desktop, Tablet, or Mobile.

dimensions.name: deviceModel
dimensions.description: The mobile device model (example: iPhone 10,6).

dimensions.name: dv360AdvertiserId
dimensions.description: The DV360 Advertiser ID that led to the key event. Identifies the DV360 advertiser.

dimensions.name: dv360AdvertiserName
dimensions.description: The DV360 Advertiser Name that led to the key event. DV360 advertisers represent real-life businesses that run advertising campaigns.

dimensions.name: dv360CampaignId
dimensions.description: The DV360 Campaign ID that led to the key event. Identifies the DV360 campaign.

dimensions.name: dv360CampaignName
dimensions.description: The DV360 Campaign Name that led to the key event. DV360 campaigns group together related insertion orders with a common business goal.

dimensions.name: dv360CreativeFormat
dimensions.description: The DV360 Creative Format that led to the key event. Also referred to as the creative type. For example, expandable, video, or native.

dimensions.name: dv360CreativeId
dimensions.description: The DV360 Creative ID that led to the key event. Identifies the DV360 creative.

dimensions.name: dv360CreativeName
dimensions.description: The DV360 Creative Name that led to the key event. The name given to a DV360 creative.

dimensions.name: dv360ExchangeId
dimensions.description: The DV360 Exchange ID that led to the key event. Identifies the DV360 exchange.

dimensions.name: dv360ExchangeName
dimensions.description: The DV360 Exchange Name that led to the key event. The DV360 ad exchange involved in the ad click. To learn more, see managing exchanges.

dimensions.name: dv360InsertionOrderId
dimensions.description: The DV360 Insertion Order ID that led to the key event. Identifies the DV360 insertion order.

dimensions.name: dv360InsertionOrderName
dimensions.description: The DV360 Insertion Order Name that led to the key event. A DV360 insertion order contains a set of line items that are related to the same advertising campaign.

dimensions.name: dv360LineItemId
dimensions.description: The DV360 Line Item ID that led to the key event. Identifies the DV360 line item.

dimensions.name: dv360LineItemName
dimensions.description: The DV360 Line Item Name that led to the key event. A DV360 line item bids on impressions and serves creatives to inventory sources.

dimensions.name: dv360Medium
dimensions.description: The DV360 Medium that led to the key event. The billable outcome of the insertion order. For example, cpm.

dimensions.name: dv360PartnerId
dimensions.description: The DV360 Partner ID that led to the key event. Identifies the DV360 partner.

dimensions.name: dv360PartnerName
dimensions.description: The DV360 Partner Name that led to the key event. DV360 partners represent agencies, trading desks, or large individual advertisers.

dimensions.name: dv360Source
dimensions.description: The DV360 Source that led to the key event. The DV360 site name where your ad was displayed.

dimensions.name: dv360SourceMedium
dimensions.description: The DV360 Source Medium that led to the key event. A combination of the source and medium.

dimensions.name: eventName
dimensions.description: The name of the event.

dimensions.name: fileExtension
dimensions.description: The extension of the downloaded file (for example, pdf or txt). Automatically populated if Enhanced Measurement is enabled. Populated by the event parameter file_extension.

dimensions.name: fileName
dimensions.description: The page path of the downloaded file (for example, /menus/dinner-menu.pdf). Automatically populated if Enhanced Measurement is enabled. Populated by the event parameter file_name.

dimensions.name: firstSessionDate
dimensions.description: The date the user's first session occurred, formatted as YYYYMMDD.

dimensions.name: firstUserCampaignId
dimensions.description: Identifier of the marketing campaign that first acquired the user. Includes Google Ads Campaigns, Manual Campaigns, & other Campaigns.

dimensions.name: firstUserCampaignName
dimensions.description: Name of the marketing campaign that first acquired the user. Includes Google Ads Campaigns, Manual Campaigns, & other Campaigns.

dimensions.name: firstUserCm360AccountId
dimensions.description: The CM360 Account ID that originally acquired the user. Identifies the CM360 account.

dimensions.name: firstUserCm360AccountName
dimensions.description: The CM360 Account Name that originally acquired the user. A CM360 account consists of advertisers, sites, campaigns, and user profiles.

dimensions.name: firstUserCm360AdvertiserId
dimensions.description: The CM360 Advertiser ID that originally acquired the user. Identifies the CM360 advertiser.

dimensions.name: firstUserCm360AdvertiserName
dimensions.description: The CM360 Advertiser Name that originally acquired the user. A CM360 Advertiser contains a group of campaigns, creative assets, and other settings.

dimensions.name: firstUserCm360CampaignId
dimensions.description: The CM360 Campaign ID that originally acquired the user. Identifies the CM360 campaign.

dimensions.name: firstUserCm360CampaignName
dimensions.description: The CM360 Campaign Name that originally acquired the user. A CM360 campaign can be configured to specify when your ads run, what landing pages are used, and other properties.

dimensions.name: firstUserCm360CreativeFormat
dimensions.description: The CM360 Creative Format that originally acquired the user. CM360 creative formats are also referred to as creative types.

dimensions.name: firstUserCm360CreativeId
dimensions.description: The CM360 Creative ID that originally acquired the user. Identifies a CM360 creative.

dimensions.name: firstUserCm360CreativeName
dimensions.description: The CM360 Creative Name that originally acquired the user. The name given to a CM360 creative.

dimensions.name: firstUserCm360CreativeType
dimensions.description: The CM360 Creative Type that originally acquired the user. A category of CM360 creatives like 'Display' or 'Tracking'. To learn more, see manage creatives

dimensions.name: firstUserCm360CreativeTypeId
dimensions.displayName: First user CM360 creative type ID
dimensions.description: The CM360 Creative Type ID that originally acquired the user. Identifies a CM360 creative type.

dimensions.name: firstUserCm360CreativeVersion
dimensions.description: The CM360 Creative Version that originally acquired the user. The version number helps you keep track of multiple versions of your creative in your reports. If you upload a new asset to an existing creative, the version number is increased by one.

dimensions.name: firstUserCm360Medium
dimensions.description: The CM360 Medium that originally acquired the user. The CM360 medium is also referred to as the placement cost structure.

dimensions.name: firstUserCm360PlacementCostStructure
dimensions.displayName: First user CM360 placement cost structure
dimensions.description: The CM360 Placement Cost Structure that originally acquired the user. Placement cost structures regulate how media cost will be calculated. For example 'CPM'.

dimensions.name: firstUserCm360PlacementId
dimensions.description: The CM360 Placement ID that originally acquired the user. Identifies a CM360 placement. A placement is the part of a website where your ad appears.

dimensions.name: firstUserCm360PlacementName
dimensions.description: The CM360 Placement Name that originally acquired the user. The given name for a CM360 placement. A placement is the part of a website where your ad appears.

dimensions.name: firstUserCm360RenderingId
dimensions.description: The CM360 Rendering ID that originally acquired the user. Identifies a CM360 creative.

dimensions.name: firstUserCm360SiteId
dimensions.description: The CM360 Site ID that originally acquired the user. Identifies a CM360 site.

dimensions.name: firstUserCm360SiteName
dimensions.description: The CM360 Site Name that originally acquired the user. The CM360 Site name from which the ad space was purchased.

dimensions.name: firstUserCm360Source
dimensions.description: The CM360 Source that originally acquired the user. The CM360 source is also referred to as the site name.

dimensions.name: firstUserCm360SourceMedium
dimensions.description: The CM360 Source Medium that originally acquired the user. A combination of the source and medium.

dimensions.name: firstUserDefaultChannelGroup
dimensions.description: The default channel group that first acquired the user. Default channel group is based primarily on source and medium. An enumeration which includes Direct, Organic Search, Paid Social, Organic Social, Email, Affiliates, Referral, Paid Search, Video, and Display.

dimensions.name: firstUserDv360AdvertiserId
dimensions.description: The DV360 Advertiser ID that originally acquired the user. Identifies the DV360 advertiser.

dimensions.name: firstUserDv360AdvertiserName
dimensions.description: The DV360 Advertiser Name that originally acquired the user. DV360 advertisers represent real-life businesses that run advertising campaigns.

dimensions.name: firstUserDv360CampaignId
dimensions.description: The DV360 Campaign ID that originally acquired the user. Identifies the DV360 campaign.

dimensions.name: firstUserDv360CampaignName
dimensions.description: The DV360 Campaign Name that originally acquired the user. DV360 campaigns group together related insertion orders with a common business goal.

dimensions.name: firstUserDv360CreativeFormat
dimensions.description: The DV360 Creative Format that originally acquired the user. Also referred to as the creative type. For example, expandable, video, or native.

dimensions.name: firstUserDv360CreativeId
dimensions.description: The DV360 Creative ID that originally acquired the user. Identifies the DV360 creative.

dimensions.name: firstUserDv360CreativeName
dimensions.description: The DV360 Creative Name that originally acquired the user. The name given to a DV360 creative.

dimensions.name: firstUserDv360ExchangeId
dimensions.description: The DV360 Exchange ID that originally acquired the user. Identifies the DV360 exchange.

dimensions.name: firstUserDv360ExchangeName
dimensions.description: The DV360 Exchange Name that originally acquired the user. The DV360 ad exchange involved in the ad click. To learn more, see managing exchanges.

dimensions.name: firstUserDv360InsertionOrderId
dimensions.displayName: First user DV360 insertion order ID
dimensions.description: The DV360 Insertion Order ID that originally acquired the user. Identifies the DV360 insertion order.

dimensions.name: firstUserDv360InsertionOrderName
dimensions.displayName: First user DV360 insertion order name
dimensions.description: The DV360 Insertion Order Name that originally acquired the user. A DV360 insertion order contains a set of line items that are related to the same advertising campaign.

dimensions.name: firstUserDv360LineItemId
dimensions.displayName: First user DV360 line item ID
dimensions.description: The DV360 Line Item ID that originally acquired the user. Identifies the DV360 line item.

dimensions.name: firstUserDv360LineItemName
dimensions.displayName: First user DV360 line item name
dimensions.description: The DV360 Line Item Name that originally acquired the user. A DV360 line item bids on impressions and serves creatives to inventory sources.

dimensions.name: firstUserDv360Medium
dimensions.description: The DV360 Medium that originally acquired the user. The billable outcome of the insertion order. For example, cpm.

dimensions.name: firstUserDv360PartnerId
dimensions.description: The DV360 Partner ID that originally acquired the user. Identifies the DV360 partner.

dimensions.name: firstUserDv360PartnerName
dimensions.description: The DV360 Partner Name that originally acquired the user. DV360 partners represent agencies, trading desks, or large individual advertisers.

dimensions.name: firstUserDv360Source
dimensions.description: The DV360 Source that originally acquired the user. The DV360 site name where your ad was displayed.

dimensions.name: firstUserDv360SourceMedium
dimensions.description: The DV360 Source Medium that originally acquired the user. A combination of the source and medium.

dimensions.name: firstUserGoogleAdsAccountName
dimensions.displayName: First user Google Ads account name
dimensions.description: The Account name from Google Ads that first acquired the user.

dimensions.name: firstUserGoogleAdsAdGroupId
dimensions.displayName: First user Google Ads ad group ID
dimensions.description: The Ad Group Id in Google Ads that first acquired the user.

dimensions.name: firstUserGoogleAdsAdGroupName
dimensions.displayName: First user Google Ads ad group name
dimensions.description: The Ad Group Name in Google Ads that first acquired the user.

dimensions.name: firstUserGoogleAdsAdNetworkType
dimensions.displayName: First user Google Ads ad network type
dimensions.description: The advertising network that first acquired the user. An enumeration which includes Google search, Search partners, Google Display Network, Youtube Search, Youtube Videos, Cross-network, Social, and (universal campaign).

dimensions.name: firstUserGoogleAdsCampaignId
dimensions.displayName: First user Google Ads campaign ID
dimensions.description: Identifier of the Google Ads marketing campaign that first acquired the user.

dimensions.name: firstUserGoogleAdsCampaignName
dimensions.description: Name of the Google Ads marketing campaign that first acquired the user.

dimensions.name: firstUserGoogleAdsCampaignType
dimensions.displayName: First user Google Ads campaign type
dimensions.description: The campaign type of the Google Ads campaign that first acquired the user. Campaign types determine where customers see your ads and the settings and options available to you in Google Ads. Campaign type is an enumeration that includes: Search, Display, Shopping, Video, Demand Gen, App, Smart, Hotel, Local, and Performance Max. To learn more, see Choose the right campaign type.

dimensions.name: firstUserGoogleAdsCreativeId
dimensions.displayName: First user Google Ads creative ID
dimensions.description: The ID of the Google Ads creative that first acquired the user. Creative IDs identify individual ads.

dimensions.name: firstUserGoogleAdsCustomerId
dimensions.displayName: First user Google Ads customer ID
dimensions.description: The Customer ID from Google Ads that first acquired the user. Customer IDs in Google Ads uniquely identify Google Ads accounts.

dimensions.name: firstUserGoogleAdsKeyword
dimensions.displayName: First user Google Ads keyword text
dimensions.description: First user Google Ads keyword text

dimensions.name: firstUserGoogleAdsQuery
dimensions.description: The search query that first acquired the user.

dimensions.name: firstUserManualAdContent
dimensions.description: The ad content that first acquired the user. Populated by the utm_content parameter.

dimensions.name: firstUserManualCampaignId
dimensions.description: The manual Campaign ID that originally acquired the user. Identifies the manual campaign. Populated by utm_id URL parameter.

dimensions.name: firstUserManualCampaignName
dimensions.description: The manual Campaign Name that originally acquired the user. The name of the manual campaign. Populated by utm_campaign URL parameter. To learn more, see Collect campaign data with custom URLs.

dimensions.name: firstUserManualCreativeFormat
dimensions.description: The manual Creative Format that originally acquired the user. Identifies the creative format used in the ad. Populated by utm_creative_format URL parameter.

dimensions.name: firstUserManualMarketingTactic
dimensions.description: The manual Marketing Tactic that originally acquired the user. The targeting criteria applied to a campaign. For example, remarketing or prospecting. Populated by utm_marketing_tactic URL parameter.

dimensions.name: firstUserManualMedium
dimensions.description: The manual Medium that originally acquired the user. The marketing medium used in the referral. For example, cpc. Populated by utm_medium URL parameter.

dimensions.name: firstUserManualSource
dimensions.description: The manual Source that originally acquired the user. The referrer. Populated by utm_source URL parameter.

dimensions.name: firstUserManualSourceMedium
dimensions.description: The manual Source Medium that originally acquired the user. A combination of the source and medium.

dimensions.name: firstUserManualSourcePlatform
dimensions.description: The manual Source Platform that originally acquired the user. The platform responsible for directing traffic to a given Analytics property. Populated by utm_source_platform URL parameter.

dimensions.name: firstUserManualTerm
dimensions.description: The term that first acquired the user. Populated by the utm_term parameter.

dimensions.name: firstUserMedium
dimensions.description: The medium that first acquired the user to your website or app.

dimensions.name: firstUserPrimaryChannelGroup
dimensions.description: The primary channel group that originally acquired a user. Primary channel groups are the channel groups used in standard reports in Google Analytics and serve as an active record of your property's data in alignment with channel grouping over time. To learn more, see Custom channel groups.

dimensions.name: firstUserSa360AdGroupId
dimensions.displayName: First user SA360 ad group ID
dimensions.description: The SA360 Ad Group ID that originally acquired the user. Identifies the SA360 ad group.

dimensions.name: firstUserSa360AdGroupName
dimensions.displayName: First user SA360 ad group name
dimensions.description: The SA360 Ad Group Name that originally acquired the user. SA360 Ad groups contain ads and keywords that relate to each other.

dimensions.name: firstUserSa360CampaignId
dimensions.description: The SA360 Campaign ID that originally acquired the user. Identifies the SA360 campaign.

dimensions.name: firstUserSa360CampaignName
dimensions.description: The SA360 Campaign Name that originally acquired the user. A SA360 campaign lets you organize your ads and define a goal for your advertising.

dimensions.name: firstUserSa360CreativeFormat
dimensions.description: The SA360 Creative Format that originally acquired the user. The creative format is the specific layout or design of the advertisement used in a campaign.

dimensions.name: firstUserSa360EngineAccountId
dimensions.displayName: First user SA360 engine account ID
dimensions.description: The SA360 Engine Account ID that originally acquired the user. Identifies the SA360 engine account.

dimensions.name: firstUserSa360EngineAccountName
dimensions.displayName: First user SA360 engine account name
dimensions.description: The SA360 Engine Account Name that originally acquired the user. A SA360 engine account contains campaigns, ad groups, and other items from an advertising account. To learn more, see SA360 engine account.

dimensions.name: firstUserSa360EngineAccountType
dimensions.displayName: First user SA360 engine account type
dimensions.description: The SA360 Engine Account Type that originally acquired the user. The type of engine used by the search engine account.

dimensions.name: firstUserSa360KeywordText
dimensions.description: The SA360 Keyword Text that originally acquired the user. The keywords that matched the search query.

dimensions.name: firstUserSa360ManagerAccountId
dimensions.displayName: First user SA360 manager account ID
dimensions.description: The SA360 Manager Account ID that originally acquired the user. Identifies the SA360 manager account.

dimensions.name: firstUserSa360ManagerAccountName
dimensions.displayName: First user SA360 manager account name
dimensions.description: The SA360 Manager Account Name that originally acquired the user. The top level of the Search Ads 360 account hierarchy and is used for administration and reporting across the lower-level sub-manager and client accounts.

dimensions.name: firstUserSa360Medium
dimensions.description: The SA360 Medium that originally acquired the user. The payment mode used in ad buying. For example, cpc.

dimensions.name: firstUserSa360Query
dimensions.description: The SA360 Query that originally acquired the user. The search query typed by the user.

dimensions.name: firstUserSa360Source
dimensions.description: The SA360 Source that originally acquired the user. The search query happened on this site.

dimensions.name: firstUserSa360SourceMedium
dimensions.description: The SA360 Source Medium that originally acquired the user. A combination of the source and medium.

dimensions.name: firstUserSource
dimensions.description: The source that first acquired the user to your website or app.

dimensions.name: firstUserSourceMedium
dimensions.description: The combined values of the dimensions firstUserSource and firstUserMedium.

dimensions.name: firstUserSourcePlatform
dimensions.description: The source platform that first acquired the user. Don't depend on this field returning Manual for traffic that uses UTMs; this field will update from returning Manual to returning (not set) for an upcoming feature launch.

dimensions.name: fullPageUrl
dimensions.description: The hostname, page path, and query string for web pages visited; for example, the fullPageUrl portion of https://www.example.com/store/contact-us?query_string=true is www.example.com/store/contact-us?query_string=true.

dimensions.name: googleAdsAccountName
dimensions.description: The Account name from Google Ads for the campaign that led to the key event. Corresponds to customer.descriptive_name in the Google Ads API.

dimensions.name: googleAdsAdGroupId
dimensions.description: The Google Ads ad group ID attributed to the key event.

dimensions.name: googleAdsAdGroupName
dimensions.description: The ad group name attributed to the key event.

dimensions.name: googleAdsAdNetworkType
dimensions.description: The advertising network type of the key event. An enumeration which includes Google search, Search partners, Google Display Network, Youtube Search, Youtube Videos, Cross-network, Social, and (universal campaign).

dimensions.name: googleAdsCampaignId
dimensions.description: The campaign ID for the Google Ads campaign attributed to the key event.

dimensions.name: googleAdsCampaignName
dimensions.description: The campaign name for the Google Ads campaign attributed to the key event.

dimensions.name: googleAdsCampaignType
dimensions.description: The campaign type for the Google Ads campaign attributed to the key event. Campaign types determine where customers see your ads and the settings and options available to you in Google Ads. Campaign type is an enumeration that includes: Search, Display, Shopping, Video, Demand Gen, App, Smart, Hotel, Local, and Performance Max. To learn more, see Choose the right campaign type.

dimensions.name: googleAdsCreativeId
dimensions.description: The ID of the Google Ads creative attributed to the key event. Creative IDs identify individual ads.

dimensions.name: googleAdsCustomerId
dimensions.description: The Customer ID from Google Ads for the campaign that led to key event. Customer IDs in Google Ads uniquely identify Google Ads accounts.

dimensions.name: googleAdsKeyword
dimensions.description: The matched keyword that led to the key event. Keywords are words or phrases describing your product or service that you choose to get your ad in front of the right customers. To learn more about Keywords, see Keywords: Definition.

dimensions.name: googleAdsQuery
dimensions.description: The search query that led to the key event.

dimensions.name: groupId
dimensions.description: The player group ID in a game for an event. Populated by the event parameter group_id.

dimensions.name: hostName
dimensions.description: Includes the subdomain and domain names of a URL; for example, the Host Name of www.example.com/contact.html is www.example.com.

dimensions.name: hour
dimensions.description: The two-digit hour of the day that the event was logged. This dimension ranges from 0-23 and is reported in your property's timezone.

dimensions.name: isKeyEvent
dimensions.description: The string true if the event is a key event. Marking an event as a key event affects reports from time of creation. It doesn't change historic data. You can mark any event as key in Google Analytics, and some events (such as first_open or purchase) are marked as key events by default.

dimensions.name: isoWeek
dimensions.description: ISO week number, where each week starts on Monday. For details, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_week_date. Example values include 01, 02, & 53.

dimensions.name: isoYear
dimensions.description: The ISO year of the event. For details, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_week_date. Example values include 2022 & 2023.

dimensions.name: isoYearIsoWeek
dimensions.description: The combined values of isoWeek and isoYear. Example values include 201652 & 201701.

dimensions.name: itemAffiliation
dimensions.description: The name or code of the affiliate (partner/vendor; if any) associated with an individual item. Populated by the affiliation item parameter.

dimensions.name: itemBrand
dimensions.description: Brand name of the item.

dimensions.name: itemCategory
dimensions.description: The hierarchical category in which the item is classified. For example, in Apparel/Mens/Summer/Shirts/T-shirts, Apparel is the item category.

dimensions.name: itemCategory2
dimensions.description: The hierarchical category in which the item is classified. For example, in Apparel/Mens/Summer/Shirts/T-shirts, Mens is the item category 2.

dimensions.name: itemCategory3
dimensions.description: The hierarchical category in which the item is classified. For example, in Apparel/Mens/Summer/Shirts/T-shirts, Summer is the item category 3.

dimensions.name: itemCategory4
dimensions.description: The hierarchical category in which the item is classified. For example, in Apparel/Mens/Summer/Shirts/T-shirts, Shirts is the item category 4.

dimensions.name: itemCategory5
dimensions.description: The hierarchical category in which the item is classified. For example, in Apparel/Mens/Summer/Shirts/T-shirts, T-shirts is the item category 5.

dimensions.name: itemId
dimensions.description: The ID of the item.

dimensions.name: itemListId
dimensions.description: The ID of the item list.

dimensions.name: itemListName
dimensions.description: The name of the item list.

dimensions.name: itemListPosition
dimensions.description: The position of an item in a list. For example, a product you sell in a list. This dimension is populated in tagging by the index parameter in the items array.

dimensions.name: itemLocationID
dimensions.description: The physical location associated with the item. For example, the physical store location. It's recommended to use the Google Place ID that corresponds to the associated item. A custom location ID can also be used. This field is populated in tagging by the location_id parameter in the items array.

dimensions.name: itemName
dimensions.description: The name of the item.

dimensions.name: itemPromotionCreativeName
dimensions.description: The name of the item-promotion creative.

dimensions.name: itemPromotionCreativeSlot
dimensions.description: The name of the promotional creative slot associated with the item. This dimension can be specified in tagging by the creative_slot parameter at the event or item level. If the parameter is specified at both the event & item level, the item-level parameter is used.

dimensions.name: itemPromotionId
dimensions.description: The ID of the item promotion.

dimensions.name: itemPromotionName
dimensions.description: The name of the promotion for the item.

dimensions.name: itemVariant
dimensions.description: The specific variation of a product. For example, XS, S, M, or L for size; or Red, Blue, Green, or Black for color. Populated by the item_variant parameter.

dimensions.name: landingPage
dimensions.description: The page path associated with the first pageview in a session.

dimensions.name: landingPagePlusQueryString
dimensions.description: The page path + query string associated with the first pageview in a session.

dimensions.name: language
dimensions.description: The language setting of the user's browser or device. For example, English.

dimensions.name: languageCode
dimensions.description: The language setting (ISO 639) of the user's browser or device. For example, en-us.

dimensions.name: level
dimensions.description: The player's level in a game. Populated by the event parameter level.

dimensions.name: linkClasses
dimensions.description: The HTML class attribute for an outbound link. For example if a user clicks a link <a class="center" href="www.youtube.com">, this dimension will return center. Automatically populated if Enhanced Measurement is enabled. Populated by the event parameter link_classes.

dimensions.name: linkDomain
dimensions.description: The destination domain of the outbound link. For example if a user clicks a link <a href="www.youtube.com">, this dimension will return youtube.com. Automatically populated if Enhanced Measurement is enabled. Populated by the event parameter link_domain.

dimensions.name: linkId
dimensions.description: The HTML ID attribute for an outbound link or file download. For example if a user clicks a link <a id="socialLinks" href="www.youtube.com">, this dimension will return socialLinks. Automatically populated if Enhanced Measurement is enabled. Populated by the event parameter link_id.

dimensions.name: linkText
dimensions.description: The link text of the file download. Automatically populated if Enhanced Measurement is enabled. Populated by the event parameter link_text.

dimensions.name: linkUrl
dimensions.description: The full URL for an outbound link or file download. For example if a user clicks a link <a href="https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=analytics">, this dimension will return https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=analytics. Automatically populated if Enhanced Measurement is enabled. Populated by the event parameter link_url.

dimensions.name: manualAdContent
dimensions.description: The ad content attributed to the key event. Populated by the utm_content parameter.

dimensions.name: manualCampaignId
dimensions.description: The manual Campaign ID that led to the key event. Identifies the manual campaign. Populated by utm_id URL parameter.

dimensions.name: manualCampaignName
dimensions.description: The manual Campaign Name that led to the key event. The name of the manual campaign. Populated by utm_campaign URL parameter. To learn more, see Collect campaign data with custom URLs.

dimensions.name: manualCreativeFormat
dimensions.description: The manual Creative Format that led to the key event. Identifies the creative format used in the ad. Populated by utm_creative_format URL parameter.

dimensions.name: manualMarketingTactic
dimensions.description: The manual Marketing Tactic that led to the key event. The targeting criteria applied to a campaign. For example, remarketing or prospecting. Populated by utm_marketing_tactic URL parameter.

dimensions.name: manualMedium
dimensions.description: The manual Medium that led to the key event. The marketing medium used in the referral. For example, cpc. Populated by utm_medium URL parameter.

dimensions.name: manualSource
dimensions.description: The manual Source that led to the key event. The referrer. Populated by utm_source URL parameter.

dimensions.name: manualSourceMedium
dimensions.description: The manual Source Medium that led to the key event. A combination of the source and medium.

dimensions.name: manualSourcePlatform
dimensions.description: The manual Source Platform that led to the key event. The platform responsible for directing traffic to a given Analytics property. Populated by utm_source_platform URL parameter.

dimensions.name: manualTerm
dimensions.description: The term attributed to the key event. Populated by the utm_term parameter.

dimensions.name: medium
dimensions.description: The medium attributed to the key event.

dimensions.name: method
dimensions.description: The method by which an event was triggered. Populated by the event parameter method.

dimensions.name: minute
dimensions.description: The two-digit minute of the hour that the event was logged. This dimension ranges from 0-59 and is reported in your property's timezone.

dimensions.name: mobileDeviceBranding
dimensions.description: Manufacturer or branded name (examples: Samsung, HTC, Verizon, T-Mobile).

dimensions.name: mobileDeviceMarketingName
dimensions.description: The branded device name (examples: Galaxy S10 or P30 Pro).

dimensions.name: mobileDeviceModel
dimensions.description: The mobile device model name (examples: iPhone X or SM-G950F).

dimensions.name: month
dimensions.description: The month of the event, a two digit integer from 01 to 12.

dimensions.name: newVsReturning
dimensions.description: New users have 0 previous sessions, and returning users have 1 or more previous sessions. This dimension returns two values: new or returning.

dimensions.name: nthDay
dimensions.description: The number of days since the start of the date range.

dimensions.name: nthHour
dimensions.description: The number of hours since the start of the date range. The starting hour is 0000.

dimensions.name: nthMinute
dimensions.description: The number of minutes since the start of the date range. The starting minute is 0000.

dimensions.name: nthMonth
dimensions.description: The number of months since the start of a date range. The starting month is 0000.

dimensions.name: nthWeek
dimensions.description: A number representing the number of weeks since the start of a date range.

dimensions.name: nthYear
dimensions.description: The number of years since the start of the date range. The starting year is 0000.

dimensions.name: operatingSystem
dimensions.description: The operating systems used by visitors to your app or website. Includes desktop and mobile operating systems such as Windows and Android.

dimensions.name: operatingSystemVersion
dimensions.description: The operating system versions used by visitors to your website or app. For example, Android 10's version is 10, and iOS 13.5.1's version is 13.5.1.

dimensions.name: operatingSystemWithVersion
dimensions.description: The operating system and version. For example, Android 10 or Windows 7.

dimensions.name: orderCoupon
dimensions.description: Code for the order-level coupon.

dimensions.name: outbound
dimensions.description: Returns true if the link led to a site that is not a part of the property's domain. Automatically populated if Enhanced Measurement is enabled. Populated by the event parameter outbound.

dimensions.name: pageLocation
dimensions.description: The protocol, hostname, page path, and query string for web pages visited; for example, the pageLocation portion of https://www.example.com/store/contact-us?query_string=true is https://www.example.com/store/contact-us?query_string=true. Populated by the event parameter page_location.

dimensions.name: pagePath
dimensions.description: The portion of the URL between the hostname and query string for web pages visited; for example, the pagePath portion of https://www.example.com/store/contact-us?query_string=true is /store/contact-us.

dimensions.name: pagePathPlusQueryString
dimensions.description: The portion of the URL following the hostname for web pages visited; for example, the pagePathPlusQueryString portion of https://www.example.com/store/contact-us?query_string=true is /store/contact-us?query_string=true.

dimensions.name: pageReferrer
dimensions.description: The full referring URL including the hostname and path. This referring URL is the user's previous URL and can be this website's domain or other domains. Populated by the event parameter page_referrer.

dimensions.name: pageTitle
dimensions.description: The web page titles used on your site.

dimensions.name: percentScrolled
dimensions.description: The percentage down the page that the user has scrolled (for example, 90). Automatically populated if Enhanced Measurement is enabled. Populated by the event parameter percent_scrolled.

dimensions.name: platform
dimensions.description: The platform on which your app or website ran; for example, web, iOS, or Android. To determine a stream's type in a report, use both platform and streamId.

dimensions.name: platformDeviceCategory
dimensions.description: The platform and type of device on which your website or mobile app ran. (example: Android / mobile)

dimensions.name: primaryChannelGroup
dimensions.description: The primary channel group attributed to the key event. Primary channel groups are the channel groups used in standard reports in Google Analytics and serve as an active record of your property's data in alignment with channel grouping over time. To learn more, see Custom channel groups.

dimensions.name: region
dimensions.description: The geographic region from which the user activity originated, derived from their IP address.

dimensions.name: sa360AdGroupId
dimensions.description: The SA360 Ad Group ID that led to the key event. Identifies the SA360 ad group.

dimensions.name: sa360AdGroupName
dimensions.description: The SA360 Ad Group Name that led to the key event. SA360 Ad groups contain ads and keywords that relate to each other.

dimensions.name: sa360CampaignId
dimensions.description: The SA360 Campaign ID that led to the key event. Identifies the SA360 campaign.

dimensions.name: sa360CampaignName
dimensions.description: The SA360 Campaign Name that led to the key event. A SA360 campaign lets you organize your ads and define a goal for your advertising.

dimensions.name: sa360CreativeFormat
dimensions.description: The SA360 Creative Format that led to the key event. The creative format is the specific layout or design of the advertisement used in a campaign.

dimensions.name: sa360EngineAccountId
dimensions.description: The SA360 Engine Account ID that led to the key event. Identifies the SA360 engine account.

dimensions.name: sa360EngineAccountName
dimensions.description: The SA360 Engine Account Name that led to the key event. A SA360 engine account contains campaigns, ad groups, and other items from an advertising account. To learn more, see SA360 engine account.

dimensions.name: sa360EngineAccountType
dimensions.description: The SA360 Engine Account Type that led to the key event. The type of engine used by the search engine account.

dimensions.name: sa360KeywordText
dimensions.description: The SA360 Keyword Text that led to the key event. The keywords that matched the search query.

dimensions.name: sa360ManagerAccountId
dimensions.description: The SA360 Manager Account ID that led to the key event. Identifies the SA360 manager account.

dimensions.name: sa360ManagerAccountName
dimensions.description: The SA360 Manager Account Name that led to the key event. The top level of the Search Ads 360 account hierarchy and is used for administration and reporting across the lower-level sub-manager and client accounts.

dimensions.name: sa360Medium
dimensions.description: The SA360 Medium that led to the key event. The payment mode used in ad buying. For example, cpc.

dimensions.name: sa360Query
dimensions.description: The SA360 Query that led to the key event. The search query typed by the user.

dimensions.name: sa360Source
dimensions.description: The SA360 Source that led to the key event. The search query happened on this site.

dimensions.name: sa360SourceMedium
dimensions.description: The SA360 Source Medium that led to the key event. A combination of the source and medium.

dimensions.name: screenResolution
dimensions.description: The screen resolution of the user's monitor. For example, 1920x1080.

dimensions.name: searchTerm
dimensions.description: The term searched by the user. For example if the user visits /some-page.html?q=some-term, this dimension returns some-term. Automatically populated if Enhanced Measurement is enabled. Populated by the event parameter search_term.

dimensions.name: sessionCampaignId
dimensions.description: The marketing campaign ID for a session. Includes Google Ads Campaigns, Manual Campaigns, & other Campaigns.

dimensions.name: sessionCampaignName
dimensions.description: The marketing campaign name for a session. Includes Google Ads Campaigns, Manual Campaigns, & other Campaigns.

dimensions.name: sessionCm360AccountId
dimensions.description: The CM360 Account ID that led to the session. Identifies the CM360 account.

dimensions.name: sessionCm360AccountName
dimensions.description: The CM360 Account Name that led to the session. A CM360 account consists of advertisers, sites, campaigns, and user profiles.

dimensions.name: sessionCm360AdvertiserId
dimensions.description: The CM360 Advertiser ID that led to the session. Identifies the CM360 advertiser.

dimensions.name: sessionCm360AdvertiserName
dimensions.description: The CM360 Advertiser Name that led to the session. A CM360 Advertiser contains a group of campaigns, creative assets, and other settings.

dimensions.name: sessionCm360CampaignId
dimensions.description: The CM360 Campaign ID that led to the session. Identifies the CM360 campaign.

dimensions.name: sessionCm360CampaignName
dimensions.description: The CM360 Campaign Name that led to the session. A CM360 campaign can be configured to specify when your ads run, what landing pages are used, and other properties.

dimensions.name: sessionCm360CreativeFormat
dimensions.description: The CM360 Creative Format that led to the session. CM360 creative formats are also referred to as creative types.

dimensions.name: sessionCm360CreativeId
dimensions.description: The CM360 Creative ID that led to the session. Identifies a CM360 creative.

dimensions.name: sessionCm360CreativeName
dimensions.description: The CM360 Creative Name that led to the session. The name given to a CM360 creative.

dimensions.name: sessionCm360CreativeType
dimensions.description: The CM360 Creative Type that led to the session. A category of CM360 creatives like 'Display' or 'Tracking'. To learn more, see manage creatives

dimensions.name: sessionCm360CreativeTypeId
dimensions.description: The CM360 Creative Type ID that led to the session. Identifies a CM360 creative type.

dimensions.name: sessionCm360CreativeVersion
dimensions.description: The CM360 Creative Version that led to the session. The version number helps you keep track of multiple versions of your creative in your reports. If you upload a new asset to an existing creative, the version number is increased by one.

dimensions.name: sessionCm360Medium
dimensions.description: The CM360 Medium that led to the session. The CM360 medium is also referred to as the placement cost structure.

dimensions.name: sessionCm360PlacementCostStructure
dimensions.description: The CM360 Placement Cost Structure that led to the session. Placement cost structures regulate how media cost will be calculated. For example 'CPM'.

dimensions.name: sessionCm360PlacementId
dimensions.description: The CM360 Placement ID that led to the session. Identifies a CM360 placement. A placement is the part of a website where your ad appears.

dimensions.name: sessionCm360PlacementName
dimensions.description: The CM360 Placement Name that led to the session. The given name for a CM360 placement. A placement is the part of a website where your ad appears.

dimensions.name: sessionCm360RenderingId
dimensions.description: The CM360 Rendering ID that led to the session. Identifies a CM360 creative.

dimensions.name: sessionCm360SiteId
dimensions.description: The CM360 Site ID that led to the session. Identifies a CM360 site.

dimensions.name: sessionCm360SiteName
dimensions.description: The CM360 Site Name that led to the session. The CM360 Site name from which the ad space was purchased.

dimensions.name: sessionCm360Source
dimensions.description: The CM360 Source that led to the session. The CM360 source is also referred to as the site name.

dimensions.name: sessionCm360SourceMedium
dimensions.description: The CM360 Source Medium that led to the session. A combination of the source and medium.

dimensions.name: sessionDefaultChannelGroup
dimensions.description: The session's default channel group is based primarily on source and medium. An enumeration which includes Direct, Organic Search, Paid Social, Organic Social, Email, Affiliates, Referral, Paid Search, Video, and Display.

dimensions.name: sessionDv360AdvertiserId
dimensions.description: The DV360 Advertiser ID that led to the session. Identifies the DV360 advertiser.

dimensions.name: sessionDv360AdvertiserName
dimensions.description: The DV360 Advertiser Name that led to the session. DV360 advertisers represent real-life businesses that run advertising campaigns.

dimensions.name: sessionDv360CampaignId
dimensions.description: The DV360 Campaign ID that led to the session. Identifies the DV360 campaign.

dimensions.name: sessionDv360CampaignName
dimensions.description: The DV360 Campaign Name that led to the session. DV360 campaigns group together related insertion orders with a common business goal.

dimensions.name: sessionDv360CreativeFormat
dimensions.description: The DV360 Creative Format that led to the session. Also referred to as the creative type. For example, expandable, video, or native.

dimensions.name: sessionDv360CreativeId
dimensions.description: The DV360 Creative ID that led to the session. Identifies the DV360 creative.

dimensions.name: sessionDv360CreativeName
dimensions.description: The DV360 Creative Name that led to the session. The name given to a DV360 creative.

dimensions.name: sessionDv360ExchangeId
dimensions.description: The DV360 Exchange ID that led to the session. Identifies the DV360 exchange.

dimensions.name: sessionDv360ExchangeName
dimensions.description: The DV360 Exchange Name that led to the session. The DV360 ad exchange involved in the ad click. To learn more, see managing exchanges.

dimensions.name: sessionDv360InsertionOrderId
dimensions.description: The DV360 Insertion Order ID that led to the session. Identifies the DV360 insertion order.

dimensions.name: sessionDv360InsertionOrderName
dimensions.description: The DV360 Insertion Order Name that led to the session. A DV360 insertion order contains a set of line items that are related to the same advertising campaign.

dimensions.name: sessionDv360LineItemId
dimensions.description: The DV360 Line Item ID that led to the session. Identifies the DV360 line item.

dimensions.name: sessionDv360LineItemName
dimensions.description: The DV360 Line Item Name that led to the session. A DV360 line item bids on impressions and serves creatives to inventory sources.

dimensions.name: sessionDv360Medium
dimensions.description: The DV360 Medium that led to the session. The billable outcome of the insertion order. For example, cpm.

dimensions.name: sessionDv360PartnerId
dimensions.description: The DV360 Partner ID that led to the session. Identifies the DV360 partner.

dimensions.name: sessionDv360PartnerName
dimensions.description: The DV360 Partner Name that led to the session. DV360 partners represent agencies, trading desks, or large individual advertisers.

dimensions.name: sessionDv360Source
dimensions.description: The DV360 Source that led to the session. The DV360 site name where your ad was displayed.

dimensions.name: sessionDv360SourceMedium
dimensions.description: The DV360 Source Medium that led to the session. A combination of the source and medium.

dimensions.name: sessionGoogleAdsAccountName
dimensions.description: The Account name from Google Ads that led to the session. Corresponds to customer.descriptive_name in the Google Ads API.

dimensions.name: sessionGoogleAdsAdGroupId
dimensions.displayName: Session Google Ads ad group ID
dimensions.description: The Ad Group Id in Google Ads for a session.

dimensions.name: sessionGoogleAdsAdGroupName
dimensions.displayName: Session Google Ads ad group name
dimensions.description: The Ad Group Name in Google Ads for a session.

dimensions.name: sessionGoogleAdsAdNetworkType
dimensions.displayName: Session Google Ads ad network type
dimensions.description: The advertising network that led to the session. An enumeration which includes Google search, Search partners, Google Display Network, Youtube Search, Youtube Videos, Cross-network, Social, and (universal campaign).

dimensions.name: sessionGoogleAdsCampaignId
dimensions.description: The Campaign ID for the Google Ads Campaign that led to this session.

dimensions.name: sessionGoogleAdsCampaignName
dimensions.description: The Campaign name for the Google Ads Campaign that led to this session.

dimensions.name: sessionGoogleAdsCampaignType
dimensions.description: The campaign type for the Google Ads campaign that led to this session. Campaign types determine where customers see your ads and the settings and options available to you in Google Ads. Campaign type is an enumeration that includes: Search, Display, Shopping, Video, Demand Gen, App, Smart, Hotel, Local, and Performance Max. To learn more, see Choose the right campaign type.

dimensions.name: sessionGoogleAdsCreativeId
dimensions.description: The ID of the Google Ads creative that led to a session on your website or app. Creative IDs identify individual ads.

dimensions.name: sessionGoogleAdsCustomerId
dimensions.description: The Customer ID from Google Ads that led to the session. Customer IDs in Google Ads uniquely identify Google Ads accounts.

dimensions.name: sessionGoogleAdsKeyword
dimensions.description: The matched keyword that led to the session. Keywords are words or phrases describing your product or service that you choose to get your ad in front of the right customers. To learn more about Keywords, see Keywords: Definition.

dimensions.name: sessionGoogleAdsQuery
dimensions.description: The search query that led to the session.

dimensions.name: sessionManualAdContent
dimensions.description: The ad content that led to a session. Populated by the utm_content parameter.

dimensions.name: sessionManualCampaignId
dimensions.description: The manual Campaign ID that led to the session. Identifies the manual campaign. Populated by utm_id URL parameter.

dimensions.name: sessionManualCampaignName
dimensions.description: The manual Campaign Name that led to the session. The name of the manual campaign. Populated by utm_campaign URL parameter. To learn more, see Collect campaign data with custom URLs.

dimensions.name: sessionManualCreativeFormat
dimensions.description: The manual Creative Format that led to the session. Identifies the creative format used in the ad. Populated by utm_creative_format URL parameter.

dimensions.name: sessionManualMarketingTactic
dimensions.description: The manual Marketing Tactic that led to the session. The targeting criteria applied to a campaign. For example, remarketing or prospecting. Populated by utm_marketing_tactic URL parameter.

dimensions.name: sessionManualMedium
dimensions.description: The manual Medium that led to the session. The marketing medium used in the referral. For example, cpc. Populated by utm_medium URL parameter.

dimensions.name: sessionManualSource
dimensions.description: The manual Source that led to the session. The referrer. Populated by utm_source URL parameter.

dimensions.name: sessionManualSourceMedium
dimensions.description: The manual Source Medium that led to the session. A combination of the source and medium.

dimensions.name: sessionManualSourcePlatform
dimensions.description: The manual Source Platform that led to the session. The platform responsible for directing traffic to a given Analytics property. Populated by utm_source_platform URL parameter.

dimensions.name: sessionManualTerm
dimensions.description: The term that led to a session. Populated by the utm_term parameter.

dimensions.name: sessionMedium
dimensions.description: The medium that initiated a session on your website or app.

dimensions.name: sessionPrimaryChannelGroup
