dimensions.description: The primary channel group that led to the session. Primary channel groups are the channel groups used in standard reports in Google Analytics and serve as an active record of your property's data in alignment with channel grouping over time. To learn more, see Custom channel groups.

dimensions.name: sessionSa360AdGroupId
dimensions.description: The SA360 Ad Group ID that led to the session. Identifies the SA360 ad group.

dimensions.name: sessionSa360AdGroupName
dimensions.description: The SA360 Ad Group Name that led to the session. SA360 Ad groups contain ads and keywords that relate to each other.

dimensions.name: sessionSa360CampaignId
dimensions.description: The SA360 Campaign ID that led to the session. Identifies the SA360 campaign.

dimensions.name: sessionSa360CampaignName
dimensions.description: The SA360 Campaign Name that led to the session. A SA360 campaign lets you organize your ads and define a goal for your advertising.

dimensions.name: sessionSa360CreativeFormat
dimensions.description: The SA360 Creative Format that led to the session. The creative format is the specific layout or design of the advertisement used in a campaign.

dimensions.name: sessionSa360EngineAccountId
dimensions.description: The SA360 Engine Account ID that led to the session. Identifies the SA360 engine account.

dimensions.name: sessionSa360EngineAccountName
dimensions.description: The SA360 Engine Account Name that led to the session. A SA360 engine account contains campaigns, ad groups, and other items from an advertising account. To learn more, see SA360 engine account.

dimensions.name: sessionSa360EngineAccountType
dimensions.description: The SA360 Engine Account Type that led to the session. The type of engine used by the search engine account. For example, google ads, bing, or baidu.

dimensions.name: sessionSa360Keyword
dimensions.description: The SA360 Keyword Text that led to the session. The keywords that matched the search query.

dimensions.name: sessionSa360ManagerAccountId
dimensions.description: The SA360 Manager Account ID that led to the session. Identifies the SA360 manager account.

dimensions.name: sessionSa360ManagerAccountName
dimensions.description: The SA360 Manager Account Name that led to the session. The top level of the Search Ads 360 account hierarchy and is used for administration and reporting across the lower-level sub-manager and client accounts.

dimensions.name: sessionSa360Medium
dimensions.description: The SA360 Medium that led to the session. The payment mode used in ad buying. For example, cpc.

dimensions.name: sessionSa360Query
dimensions.description: The SA360 Query that led to the session. The search query typed by the user.

dimensions.name: sessionSa360Source
dimensions.description: The SA360 Source that led to the session. The search query happened on this site.

dimensions.name: sessionSa360SourceMedium
dimensions.description: The SA360 Source Medium that led to the session. A combination of the source and medium.

dimensions.name: sessionSource
dimensions.description: The source that initiated a session on your website or app.

dimensions.name: sessionSourceMedium
dimensions.description: The combined values of the dimensions sessionSource and sessionMedium.

dimensions.name: sessionSourcePlatform
dimensions.description: The source platform of the session's campaign. Don't depend on this field returning Manual for traffic that uses UTMs; this field will update from returning Manual to returning (not set) for an upcoming feature launch.

dimensions.name: shippingTier
dimensions.description: The shipping tier selected for delivery of the purchased item. For example, Ground, Air, or Next-day. Populated by the shipping_tier event parameter.

dimensions.name: signedInWithUserId
dimensions.description: The string yes if the user signed in with the User-ID feature. To learn more about User-ID, see Measure activity across platforms with User-ID.

dimensions.name: source
dimensions.description: The source attributed to the key event.

dimensions.name: sourceMedium
dimensions.description: The combined values of the dimensions source and medium.

dimensions.name: sourcePlatform
dimensions.description: The source platform of the key event's campaign. Don't depend on this field returning Manual for traffic that uses UTMs; this field will update from returning Manual to returning (not set) for an upcoming feature launch.

dimensions.name: streamId
dimensions.description: The numeric data stream identifier for your app or website.

dimensions.name: streamName
dimensions.description: The data stream name for your app or website.

dimensions.name: testDataFilterId
dimensions.description: The numeric identifier of a data filter in testing state. You use data filters to include or exclude event data from your reports based on event-parameter values. To learn more, see Data filters.

dimensions.name: testDataFilterName
dimensions.description: The name of data filters in testing state. You use data filters to include or exclude event data from your reports based on event-parameter values. To learn more, see Data filters.

dimensions.name: transactionId
dimensions.description: The ID of the ecommerce transaction.

dimensions.name: unifiedPagePathScreen
dimensions.description: The page path (web) or screen class (app) on which the event was logged.

dimensions.name: unifiedPageScreen
dimensions.displayName: Page path + query string and screen class
dimensions.description: The page path and query string (web) or screen class (app) on which the event was logged.

dimensions.name: unifiedScreenClass
dimensions.description: The page title (web) or screen class (app) on which the event was logged.

dimensions.name: unifiedScreenName
dimensions.description: The page title (web) or screen name (app) on which the event was logged.

dimensions.name: userAgeBracket
dimensions.description: User age brackets.

dimensions.name: userGender
dimensions.description: User gender.

dimensions.name: videoProvider
dimensions.description: The source of the video (for example, youtube). Automatically populated for embedded videos if Enhanced Measurement is enabled. Populated by the event parameter video_provider.

dimensions.name: videoTitle
dimensions.description: The title of the video. Automatically populated for embedded videos if Enhanced Measurement is enabled. Populated by the event parameter video_title.

dimensions.name: videoUrl
dimensions.description: The URL of the video. Automatically populated for embedded videos if Enhanced Measurement is enabled. Populated by the event parameter video_url.

dimensions.name: virtualCurrencyName
dimensions.description: The name of a virtual currency with which the user is interacting. Such as spending or purchasing gems in a game. Populated by the virtual_currency_name event parameter.

dimensions.name: visible
dimensions.description: Returns true if the content is visible. Automatically populated for embedded videos if Enhanced Measurement is enabled. Populated by the event parameter visible.

dimensions.name: week
dimensions.description: The week of the event, a two-digit number from 01 to 53. Each week starts on Sunday. January 1st is always in week 01. The first and last week of the year have fewer than 7 days in most years. Weeks other than the first and the last week of the year always have 7 days. For years where January 1st is a Sunday, the first week of that year and the last week of the prior year have 7 days.

dimensions.name: year
dimensions.description: The four-digit year of the event. For example, 2020 or 2024.

dimensions.name: yearMonth
dimensions.description: The combined values of year and month. Example values include 202212 or 202301.

dimensions.name: yearWeek
dimensions.description: The combined values of year and week. Example values include 202253 or 202301.
